								<h2>Token :</h2>
								<p> 1.	All tokens are single journey tokens that are valid only for a one way journey.<br>
									2.	The minimum cost of travelling on the Metro is Rs 8/-.<br>
									3.	The maximum cost of travelling on the Metro is Rs 30/-.<br>
									4.	The value of the token will depend on the destination.<br>
									5.	It is valid only till the day of purchase.<br>
    								6.	Token fare can be calculated by using the Fare Calculator or viewing the Fare Chart from this link- Lucknow Metro Rail
    							</p>
								<h2>Travel Card (Smart Card):</h2>
								<p>
									1.	It is a most convenient option for the frequent commuter.<br/>
									2.	The Minimum recharge value of a travel card is Rs. 100/- and the maximum is Rs. 1000/-. Subsequent recharge will be in multiple of Rs. 50/-.<br/>
									3.	Security Deposit of Rs 50/- payable at purchase (refundable on return of card).<br/>
									4.	It is valid for one year from the date of purchase or one year from the date of recharge whichever is later.<br/>
									5.	There will be a charge of Rs 5/- on renewal of Smart Card.<br/>
									6.	Ticket Reading Machines are available at all Metro Stations. This facility helps commuters to check the balance on their Smart Card.<br/>
								</p>
								<h2>Tourist Card:</h2>
								<p>.
									1.	This card is for unlimited travel over short periods.<br/>
									2.	There are two kinds of cards - 1 day and 3 day.<br/>
									3.	Value of 1-Day Card: Rs 100/-<br/>
									4.	Value of 3-Day Card: Rs 250/-<br/>
									5.	Security Deposit of Rs 50/- payable at purchase (refundable on return of card).<br/>
								</p>
